2:T410,{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Swing vs. Sliding Gates: The Ultimate Buyer's Guide","description":"Short on space? Find out whether swing gates or sliding gates are better for your London property based on driveway size, slope, and security.","url":"https://www.drivewaygateslondon.co.uk/guides/swing-vs-sliding-gates/","datePublished":"2026-02-07","dateModified":"2026-02-07","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.drivewaygateslondon.co.uk/images/gates/gate-aluminium-swing-open-luxury-garden.png","width":1200,"height":630},"author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"Driveway Gates London","url":"https://www.drivewaygateslondon.co.uk"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"Driveway Gates London","url":"https://www.drivewaygateslondon.co.uk","logo":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.drivewaygateslondon.co.uk/android-chrome-512x512.png","width":512,"height":512}},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.drivewaygateslondon.co.uk/guides/swing-vs-sliding-gates/"}}3:T634,{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"Can swing gates open outward onto the pavement in London?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Generally no. UK regulations prevent gates from opening outward over a public footpath or highway. Swing gates on London residential properties almost always open inward. If inward opening is not possible due to driveway geometry, sliding gates or bi-folding gates are the practical alternative."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How much wall space do I need for a sliding gate?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"For a tracked sliding gate, you need clear wall or fence space equal to the gate width plus approximately 500mm on one side of the opening. For a 4-metre gate, that means approximately 4.5 metres of unobstructed boundary."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Are sliding gates more secure than swing gates?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Both types offer equivalent security when properly specified. Sliding gates have one advantage: they cannot be forced inward by a vehicle ramming from outside, as the gate must travel laterally rather than hinging."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Which type of gate is cheaper to automate?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Swing gates are generally less expensive to automate than sliding gates. A pair of swing gates with ram-arm motors typically costs £1,200 to £2,200 to automate. A sliding gate with rack-and-pinion motor and track typically costs £1,500 to £2,800, plus any groundwork for the track bed."}}]}6:["slug","swing-vs-sliding-gates","d"]
